cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.ST, cs.CL

This paper deals with the problem of uncertainty calibration in machine learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the experiments in this paper focus on image classification tasks, cs.CV is likely the most relevant sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI.
